title: For Sale:  The Challenge
postcontent:
Can you shoot 4 MOA rapid fire without a bipod or rest?  Can you do it with a rack-grade rifle and surplus ammo?  Can you do it with iron sights?  Join us for an Appleseed Rifle Marksmanship clinic and find out.

See if you can answer these questions - which every American who loves his country should be able to answer:
1. When and where was the American Revolution won, according to John Adams?
2. When and where did the Revolutionary War break out?
3. What caused the British Regulars, the most well-trained, well-disciplined army in the world, to break and run at Concord's North Bridge, after only two minutes of musket fire by shopkeepers and farmers?
4.  What caused this reversal of British military opinion:

BEFORE April 19, 1775:
"Americans are raw, undisciplined and cowardly". John Montagu, 4th Earl of Sandwich and 1st Lord of the Admiralty 

"With a thousand British grenadiers I would undertake to go from one end of America to the other and geld all the males, partly by force and partly with a little coaxing". Major General Alured Clarke 

AFTER April 19, 1775:
"Whoever looks upon them as an irregular mob, will find himself very much mistaken. They have men amongst them who know very well what they are about..." Lieutenant-General Hugh Percy, 2nd Duke of Northumberland

Join us for the Appleseed Rifle Marksmanship Clinic, Sep 1-2, 2012 at the Bluegrass Sportsmen’s League in Wilmore, KY and find out the answers to these basic questions about our country's founding.

National Website: http://www.appleseedinfo.org/

Kentucky Appleseed Facebook Page: http://www.facebook.com/KentuckyRifleman

postcontent: FAL built by Springfield Arms in Geneseo, Illinois, in the original T48 series configuration, seldom seen for sale.  It's in .308 and has two twenty round mags and is in great USED condition.  This is the SAR48 (Springfield Armory Rifle) MATCH receiver (built to avoid ban so is stamped SAR 4800 on opposite side of receiver) and has not been 'tinkered' with.  I believe these were built with inch parts, but not certain.  It is not the Israeli version that's much bulkier.  I've owned this for years and seldom took it out of the gun safe.  As with the original FN battle rifle (the Right Hand of the Free World), this has the gas piston operation and adjustable gas valving that makes the rifle so incredibly reliable and pleasant to shoot.  I don't have a better camera, so the photos you see are all I can provide.  The VW in the background does NOT go with the rifle.  Ebay generally has at least one or two of the SUIT scope/mount units that look great on these rifles for under $400 which would add a great deal of value to this piece.   Don't confuse this with the Century Arms mixed mfr parts guns.  This is not an inflated or desperation price.  Prefer not to ship.  Note: I'll accept an exc to new Rem 700 VTR in .308 as partial payment on this. Thanks for looking.
